description: From Middle English unwittinge, unwitand, from Old English unwitende (“unwitting; not knowing; unaware; unconscious”), from Proto-Germanic *unwitandz (“not knowing”), equivalent to un- +‎ witting. Cognate with West Frisian ûnwittend, Dutch onwetend, German Low German unwetend, German unwissend and unwissentlich, Icelandic óvitandi.

adjectives.description: unwitting (comparative more unwitting, superlative most unwitting)

examples: Synonyms: clueless, ignorant; see also Thesaurus:ignorant
Some people, apparently, have thought about it and reached the conclusion that every case of being misinformed is unwitting.
